In this statement, President Barack Obama discusses the release of the Nuclear Posture Review, which outlines the United States' strategy to reduce the role of nuclear weapons in national security. The review recognizes that the greatest threats to global security are nuclear terrorism and proliferation. The United States is prioritizing efforts to prevent nuclear proliferation and terrorism, aligning policies with the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty, and increasing funding for programs to prevent the spread of nuclear weapons. The United States also declares that it will not use or threaten to use nuclear weapons against non-nuclear weapons states that comply with their nonproliferation obligations. Additionally, the United States commits to not conducting nuclear testing, seeking ratification of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, and not developing new nuclear warheads or capabilities. The statement emphasizes the importance of maintaining a safe and effective nuclear deterrent while also strengthening conventional capabilities. Overall, the United States aims to work towards a future where nuclear weapons do not exist by reducing arsenals, securing vulnerable nuclear materials, and strengthening the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty.